### What's a Heuristic:
A heuristic is a technique to solve a problem more quickly and efficiently when an exact solution is not feasible or too time-consuming. In the context of the bin packing problem, the priority function is a heuristic that decides the order in which bins are considered for placing an item.

### The Loss Function:
The loss is calculated as the average of the maximum bin utilization after adding the item, minus the maximum possible minimum loss. It is a measure of how well the heuristic performs.

