- Focus on mathematical expressions that can be vectorized using numpy operations.
- Each function should return an array of the same size as the bins.

### Final Note:
The functions will be used in a heuristic algorithm, so the priority scores should ideally reflect some measure of how well the item fits into each bin.

### Example of a Bin Packing Heuristic:
The First Fit Decreasing heuristic sorts the items in decreasing order and tries to place each item into the first bin that can accommodate it. The priority function in this case would give higher priority to bins that have more remaining capacity and are more similar in size to the item.

### Conclusion:
By following these guidelines, you can create 10 unique and valid priority functions that can be used in different heuristics for the bin packing problem.
